textfield.text:
Flash memory is non-volatile computer storage chip ,that can be electrically erased and reprogrammed.
There are two types Flash memory classified on the basis of chip used. 1)SLC(Single Level Chip) 2)MLC(Multi level Chip)
They are compact. They are Non-Volatile. Does not generate significant heat. Requires less power to operate. Shock Resistance and Read, write latencies are very low
Erase-before-write Limitation on the maximum number of erase/program cycles Asymmetric operations speed

textfield.text: GroupFTL reduces space demand for caching mapping table GroupFTL exploits only readily available spatial locality GroupFTL does not impose strict mapping rule and hence does not impose additional garbage collection cost. As with help of GroupFTL we can write whole block , if a cache is available ,so in future a efficient caching algorithm can be implemented to achieve better hit ratio in cache.
